## Custom Metric Dimensions in Tyk Gateway OTLP Metrics

Tyk Gateway lets you define **custom metric instruments** via `opentelemetry.metrics.api_metrics` in the gateway config. Each instrument can attach labels from **7 dimension sources** — enabling rich observability without modifying backend services.

| Source | What it provides | Example keys |
|---|---|---|
| `metadata` | Built-in request fields (12 keys) | `method`, `response_code`, `api_id`, `api_name`, `org_id`, `response_flag`, `ip_address`, `api_version`, `host`, `scheme`, `listen_path`, `endpoint` |
| `session` | Authenticated session fields (5 keys) | `api_key` (last 6 chars ⚠️), `oauth_id`, `alias`, `portal_app`, `portal_org` |
| `header` | Any HTTP **request** header | `X-Customer-ID`, `X-Tenant-ID`, `Authorization` |
| `context` | Tyk [context variables](https://tyk.io/docs/api-management/traffic-transformation/request-context-variables) | `jwt_claims_tier`, `request_id`, `path_parts` |
| `response_header` | Any upstream **response** header (success path only) | `X-Cache-Status`, `X-Backend-Version` |
| `gateway` | Gateway instance metadata (set at startup) | `node_id`, `node_version`, `group_id`, `tags` |
| `config_data` | API definition metadata from the `config_data` map | Any key set on the API definition |

**Max 10 dimensions per instrument** (OTel SDK fast path). High-cardinality sources (session/headers on histograms) emit a startup warning.

```json
// Example: opentelemetry.metrics.api_metrics in tyk.conf
[
  {
    "name": "tyk.requests.by_customer",
    "type": "counter",
    "description": "Request count by customer and subscription tier",
    "dimensions": [
      { "source": "header",   "key": "X-Customer-ID",   "label": "customer_id", "default": "unknown" },
      { "source": "context",  "key": "jwt_claims_tier", "label": "tier",        "default": "standard" },
      { "source": "metadata", "key": "api_id",          "label": "api_id" }
    ],
    "filters": { "api_ids": ["payments-api", "orders-api"] }
  },
  {
    "name": "tyk.latency.premium_tier",
    "type": "histogram",
    "histogram_source": "total",
    "histogram_buckets": [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1, 2.5, 5],
    "dimensions": [
      { "source": "context",  "key": "jwt_claims_tier", "label": "tier" },
      { "source": "metadata", "key": "api_id",          "label": "api_id" }
    ],
    "filters": { "methods": ["POST", "PUT"], "status_codes": ["2xx"] }
  }
]
```

> **Panels in the sections below will show "No data" until custom instruments are configured in the gateway.** Each section includes the exact config snippet needed to populate it.
